Place the largest value (1.0) as the first item in the list. Then, arrange the other values by going counter-clockwise around the pie starting from the slice marked 1.0. Format the answer as [1.0, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.0], where each number is the normalized percentage of each slice. No explanation needed.
